00:39:13,401 --> 00:39:15,164
- The little guy, Napoleon.
- Uh-huh.

477
00:39:15,336 --> 00:39:19,329
He was on one side
and a duke was on the other.

478
00:39:19,507 --> 00:39:20,997
Duke of Wellington.

479
00:39:21,175 --> 00:39:24,235
Yeah, and the Duke of Wellington,
he had Russians helping him.

480
00:39:24,412 --> 00:39:25,436
Prussians.

481
00:39:39,693 --> 00:39:44,426
Enough with the rugby shirts.
You look like a giant bumblebee.

482
00:39:46,767 --> 00:39:47,995
SJ:
That Taco Bell.

483
00:39:48,169 --> 00:39:51,935
KFC catty-corner. And
the Long John Silver's on the next block.

484
00:39:52,106 --> 00:39:53,130
MICHAEL:
You own all of them?

485
00:39:53,307 --> 00:39:56,037
- Yeah. We've got like hundreds.
- Eighty-five.

486
00:39:56,310 --> 00:39:58,505
Is that why Mr. Tuohy
don't have to go to work?

487
00:39:58,746 --> 00:40:02,705
Whoa, whoa! Hey! I'm working even
when I'm not working.

488
00:40:03,451 --> 00:40:06,545
- What?
- And you eat at all these places for free?

489
00:40:06,720 --> 00:40:08,688
All you want. It's awesome.

490
00:40:08,856 --> 00:40:11,791
What do y'all do with all
the leftover food from the restaurant?

491
00:40:11,959 --> 00:40:14,325
We have to throw some out,
what's already cooked.

492
00:40:14,495 --> 00:40:17,293
- That's too bad.
- Yeah, I'd rather sell it.

493
00:40:17,465 --> 00:40:19,797
Seems like you could give it away
or something.

494
00:40:19,967 --> 00:40:23,767
- You should check into that, Daddy.
SEAN: All right, I will, SJ.

495
00:40:23,938 --> 00:40:26,736
How come we're not eating
at one of your restaurants tonight?

496
00:40:26,907 --> 00:40:30,365
- Well, because tonight is a special occasion.
SJ: What?

497
00:40:30,911 --> 00:40:34,369
I talked to Coach Cotton. He said
Michael's grades have improved enough...

498
00:40:34,548 --> 00:40:37,381
...that he can go out
for spring football in March.

499
00:40:37,551 --> 00:40:40,918
- Isn't that great?
- Oh, man! You're gonna crush some people!

500
00:40:41,522 --> 00:40:43,251
[SEAN CHUCKLES]

501
00:40:48,262 --> 00:40:51,060
- Hey, guys, how we doing?
- Great, thank you.

502
00:40:51,932 --> 00:40:55,390
I've got a design book I need to get.
Why don't you check our reservation?

503
00:40:55,569 --> 00:40:57,469
They'll seat us right away.
Can't it wait?

504
00:40:57,638 --> 00:41:00,106
They might be closed by then.
Come on, SJ!

505
00:41:00,274 --> 00:41:01,798
I need some new magazines.

506
00:41:04,178 --> 00:41:06,078
Michael, come on. Come on.

507
00:41:17,224 --> 00:41:20,557
Collins? Collins?

508
00:41:21,028 --> 00:41:23,553
Collins, come on, your dad's
already PO'd. Let's go.

509
00:41:23,731 --> 00:41:24,925
COLLINS:
Over here.

510
00:41:26,534 --> 00:41:28,661
[COLLINS CHUCKLING]

511
00:41:28,836 --> 00:41:30,929
[CHATTERING]

512
00:41:33,307 --> 00:41:38,006
You remember this one, Mom?
You read it to us like a thousand times.

513
00:41:38,412 --> 00:41:42,109
"He gnashed his terrible teeth
and he roared his terrible roar."

514
00:41:43,184 --> 00:41:45,084
I always liked this one.

515
00:41:45,252 --> 00:41:46,617
Mm. Ferdinand.

516
00:41:46,921 --> 00:41:48,752
Me too.

517
00:41:48,956 --> 00:41:52,448
Michael, your mama ever read
either one of those books to you?

518
00:41:55,696 --> 00:41:57,254
No?

519
00:41:57,965 --> 00:41:59,523
COLLINS:
How cute!

520
00:41:59,700 --> 00:42:01,190
SEAN:
It was a good steak, huh?

521
00:42:01,368 --> 00:42:02,357
COLLINS:
Thank you, Daddy.

522
00:42:02,536 --> 00:42:04,094
LEIGH ANNE:
Thank you for a lovely dinner, Papa.

523
00:42:04,271 --> 00:42:05,636
SEAN:
Here we go.

524
00:42:20,821 --> 00:42:22,812
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

525
00:42:40,841 --> 00:42:45,574
Michael. Who was that boy
you were talking to at the restaurant?

526
00:42:45,746 --> 00:42:47,714
Marcus.

527
00:42:48,382 --> 00:42:52,478
- Marcus, and he... He works there?
- Yeah.

528
00:42:53,587 --> 00:42:55,418
How do you know him?

529
00:42:56,957 --> 00:42:59,152
He's my brother.

530
00:43:05,699 --> 00:43:08,600
Well, we'd really... We'd really
like to meet him someday.

531
00:43:09,837 --> 00:43:12,135
Would that be okay with you?

532
00:43:12,606 --> 00:43:14,540
MICHAEL:
I don't know where he stays.

533
00:43:15,242 --> 00:43:17,733
LEIGH ANNE:
When was the last time you saw him?

534
00:43:20,581 --> 00:43:22,139
When I was little, maybe.

535
00:43:26,787 --> 00:43:30,848
LEIGH ANNE: "Once upon a time in Spain,
there was a little bull...

536
00:43:31,025 --> 00:43:34,188
...and his name was Ferdinand.

537
00:43:34,561 --> 00:43:37,860
All the other little bulls he lived with
would run and jump...

538
00:43:38,032 --> 00:43:40,762
...and butt their heads together.

539
00:43:41,402 --> 00:43:43,927
But not Ferdinand.

540
00:43:45,105 --> 00:43:50,907
He liked to sit just quietly
and smell the flowers.

541
00:43:52,012 --> 00:43:55,812
He had a favorite spot out
in the pasture under a cork tree.

542
00:43:57,418 --> 00:43:59,545
LEIGH ANNE:
It was his favorite tree...

543
00:43:59,720 --> 00:44:05,283
...and he would sit in its shade
all day and smell the flowers."

544
00:44:05,459 --> 00:44:08,223
- Good night.
- Good night.

545
00:44:10,597 --> 00:44:13,191
- What?
- What?

546
00:44:13,467 --> 00:44:15,594
Why are you smiling?

547
00:44:15,869 --> 00:44:20,238
I don't know, I'm just happy.
Real happy.

548
00:44:20,407 --> 00:44:23,376
Does this happiness have anything
to do with Michael?

549
00:44:23,544 --> 00:44:25,171
No.

550
00:44:25,979 --> 00:44:28,880
It has everything to do with Michael.

551
00:44:30,250 --> 00:44:32,741
Mm. Mm.

552
00:44:32,986 --> 00:44:34,954
- Happy's good.
- Mm.

553
00:44:35,456 --> 00:44:37,583
You know what I think we should do?

554
00:44:37,758 --> 00:44:40,556
We should start a charity
for kids like Michael.

555
00:44:40,728 --> 00:44:43,162
- Okay.
- Maybe fund a program at Wingate.

556
00:44:43,330 --> 00:44:44,354
Sure.

557
00:44:44,531 --> 00:44:46,795
Lord knows that school
could use a little color.

558
00:44:46,967 --> 00:44:50,562
Poor Michael's like a fly in the milk
in that place.

559
00:44:50,738 --> 00:44:52,638
Are you listening to me?

560
00:44:54,475 --> 00:44:59,105
- Hmm?
- I try to concentrate on one...

561
00:44:59,913 --> 00:45:01,574
...thing...

562
00:45:02,015 --> 00:45:03,676
...at a time.

563
00:45:03,851 --> 00:45:05,546
[WHISPERING]
You knew I was a multitasker...

564
00:45:05,719 --> 00:45:07,084
...when you married me, right?

565
00:45:07,254 --> 00:45:11,315
- I sure did.
- Right. Okay, just checking.

566
00:45:15,129 --> 00:45:19,498
Okay, Tuohy family.
Big smiles, everyone.

567
00:45:20,300 --> 00:45:24,202
And one, two, three!

568
00:45:26,640 --> 00:45:27,664
Michael.

569
00:45:27,841 --> 00:45:29,968
Come on down here
and get in the next one.

570
00:45:30,177 --> 00:45:33,169
Come on. Come on. Come on down.

571
00:45:38,519 --> 00:45:41,579
Oh, come on. It's not like I'm gonna
put it on the Christmas card.

572
00:45:41,755 --> 00:45:46,055
Okay, let's scootch in a little tighter.

573
00:45:46,226 --> 00:45:47,750
That's good.

574
00:45:48,529 --> 00:45:49,860
Really big smiles.

575
00:45:50,030 --> 00:45:52,692
Okay, one, two, three.

576
00:45:52,866 --> 00:45:54,663
- Say "Rebels!"
ALL: Rebels!

577
00:45:58,872 --> 00:46:01,397
ANNOUNCER [ON TV]: A blitz off
the corner, quick pass over the middle.

578
00:46:01,575 --> 00:46:05,841
- The hot route was there. And that's...
LEIGH ANNE: I got it.

579
00:46:06,513 --> 00:46:08,845
- Who's winning?
- Tennessee.

580
00:46:09,016 --> 00:46:11,678
- Ugh. Who they playing?
- Clemson.

581
00:46:11,852 --> 00:46:14,514
Your mama roots against Tennessee
no matter who they play?

582
00:46:14,688 --> 00:46:17,122
Uh... Yes, I do. With gusto.

583
00:46:17,291 --> 00:46:19,191
She can't stand Tennessee.

584
00:46:19,359 --> 00:46:22,419
Collie-bell, I thought you were
going over to your boyfriend's.

585
00:46:22,596 --> 00:46:24,461
Thought I'd hang around here
for the day.

586
00:46:25,332 --> 00:46:26,765
Hmm.

587
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:28,558
I like that.

588
00:46:28,735 --> 00:46:31,636
There's a couple messages on the machine.
I didn't check them.

589
00:46:31,805 --> 00:46:33,238
LEIGH ANNE:
All right.

590
00:46:34,208 --> 00:46:37,609
BOBBY: Hey, Sean, hey, Leigh Anne, it's
your cousin Bobby. Happy New Year's.

591
00:46:37,845 --> 00:46:40,712
- Listen, I've had about five cold ones...
- Of course you have.

592
00:46:40,881 --> 00:46:42,940
...so I'm just gonna go ahead and ask:

593
00:46:43,517 --> 00:46:46,850
Did y'all know there's a colored boy
in your Christmas card?

594
00:46:48,422 --> 00:46:49,548
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

595
00:46:49,890 --> 00:46:51,619
What?

596
00:46:52,226 --> 00:46:55,218
You just looked teeny-tiny next to him.

597
00:46:55,395 --> 00:46:57,363
Right? Like Jessica Lange and King Kong.

598
00:46:57,531 --> 00:46:58,589
[WOMEN LAUGHING]

599
00:46:58,765 --> 00:47:01,359
Hey, does Michael get
the family discount at Taco Bell?

600
00:47:01,535 --> 00:47:05,062
Because if he does,
Sean's gonna lose a few stores.

601
00:47:05,239 --> 00:47:06,297
He's a good kid.

602
00:47:06,473 --> 00:47:09,408
Well, I say you make it official
and just adopt him.

603
00:47:09,576 --> 00:47:11,009
[WOMEN LAUGHING]

604
00:47:11,178 --> 00:47:15,478
He's gonna be 18 in a few months. Doesn't
really make much sense to legally adopt.

605
00:47:18,652 --> 00:47:19,676
Leigh Anne.

606
00:47:20,153 --> 00:47:22,678
Is this some sort of white-guilt thing?

607
00:47:23,023 --> 00:47:25,321
ELAINE:
What will your daddy say?

608
00:47:26,026 --> 00:47:29,325
Um... Before or after
he turns over in his grave?

609
00:47:29,496 --> 00:47:31,964
Daddy's been gone five years, Elaine.

610
00:47:32,132 --> 00:47:35,260
Make matters worse, you were
at the funeral. Remember?

611
00:47:35,435 --> 00:47:37,801
You wore Chanel
and that awful black hat.

612
00:47:37,971 --> 00:47:39,768
Look, here's the deal.

613
00:47:39,940 --> 00:47:43,171
I don't need y'all to approve
my choices, all right?

614
00:47:43,343 --> 00:47:47,507
But I do ask that you respect them. You
have no idea what this boy's been through.

615
00:47:47,681 --> 00:47:50,343
And if this is gonna become
some running diatribe...

616
00:47:50,517 --> 00:47:53,213
...I can find an overpriced salad
a lot closer to home.

617
00:47:55,222 --> 00:47:58,589
- Leigh Anne, I'm sorry. We didn't intend to...
- No, we didn't, really.

618
00:47:58,759 --> 00:48:01,990
BETH:
I think what you're doing is so great.

619
00:48:02,162 --> 00:48:04,926
To open up your home to him?

620
00:48:05,299 --> 00:48:07,563
Honey, you're changing that boy's life.

621
00:48:08,402 --> 00:48:09,994
No.

622
00:48:10,537 --> 00:48:12,129
He's changing mine.

623
00:48:13,707 --> 00:48:16,039
And that's awesome for you,
but what about Collins?

624
00:48:17,878 --> 00:48:20,176
- What about Collins?
ELAINE: Aren't you worried?

625
00:48:20,347 --> 00:48:22,042
I mean, even just a little?

626
00:48:22,215 --> 00:48:26,652
He's a boy, a large, black boy,
sleeping under the same roof.

627
00:48:29,356 --> 00:48:30,653
Shame on you.

628
00:48:35,862 --> 00:48:37,193
I've got this.

629
00:48:39,299 --> 00:48:41,096
LEIGH ANNE:
Be honest with me, okay?

630
00:48:43,003 --> 00:48:46,666
Does Michael being here
make you uncomfortable?

631
00:48:47,307 --> 00:48:50,743
They're stupid kids.
Who cares what they say?

632
00:48:50,911 --> 00:48:54,074
- What kids?
- At school.

633
00:48:54,581 --> 00:48:55,912
They're juvenile.

634
00:48:56,083 --> 00:48:58,108
And what do the juvenile kids say?

635
00:48:59,186 --> 00:49:01,416
It's really not worth repeating.

636
00:49:02,556 --> 00:49:04,456
And don't worry about SJ.

637
00:49:04,758 --> 00:49:08,956
He likes all the attention. He introduces
Michael as his big brother.

638
00:49:13,667 --> 00:49:15,032
And what about you?

639
00:49:15,435 --> 00:49:17,403
It's fine.

640
00:49:19,206 --> 00:49:22,300
I mean, you can't just throw him
out on the street.

641
00:49:22,476 --> 00:49:24,637
I could make other arrangements.

642
00:49:28,649 --> 00:49:31,209
GIRL: Hi, Mike.
- Hi. Need a push?

643
00:49:31,385 --> 00:49:33,012
Yes.

644
00:49:38,091 --> 00:49:40,616
MICHAEL: Oh.
GIRL: Higher, Mike, higher!

645
00:49:40,794 --> 00:49:44,230
[MICHAEL & GIRLS CHUCKLING]

646
00:49:44,431 --> 00:49:46,422
GIRL:
Higher!

647
00:49:48,669 --> 00:49:50,159
[GIRL GIGGLING]

648
00:49:50,637 --> 00:49:52,798
Higher!

649
00:49:53,707 --> 00:49:56,141
[MICHAEL & GIRLS CHUCKLING]

650
00:49:56,476 --> 00:49:59,604
GIRL:
Don't look down, don't look down. Ah!

651
00:49:59,780 --> 00:50:00,804
[MICHAEL CHUCKLES]

652
00:50:32,846 --> 00:50:35,815
- Where are you going?
- Collins?

653
00:50:47,427 --> 00:50:49,725
Quit looking at me like that.

654
00:50:49,896 --> 00:50:52,831
I mean, we study together at home.

655
00:51:09,549 --> 00:51:14,009
You know how much those things weigh?
This kid's gonna make us all famous.

656
00:51:14,187 --> 00:51:15,552
[CHUCKLES]

657
00:51:15,722 --> 00:51:19,954
Easy, Bert, man. It's only the spring.
He hasn't even had his first practice yet.

658
00:51:20,127 --> 00:51:22,152
No, he's a player.

659
00:51:22,596 --> 00:51:24,086
PLAYERS:
Break!

660
00:51:24,564 --> 00:51:26,532
QB: Ready.
PLAYERS: Break!

661
00:51:27,134 --> 00:51:30,797
COTTON: Get down, son.
Get down in your stance. In your stance!

662
00:51:31,071 --> 00:51:32,095
QB:
Go!

663
00:51:33,306 --> 00:51:37,072
COTTON:
Shuck him, shuck him! Ah, ah...

664
00:51:38,145 --> 00:51:41,239
Mike, son, you...
You fought off the block...

665
00:51:41,414 --> 00:51:43,746
...but then you wanna shuck
the blocker.

666
00:51:43,917 --> 00:51:46,886
All right? Shuck him. All right, let's go.

667
00:51:47,687 --> 00:51:49,416
QB:
Huddle up.

668
00:51:49,589 --> 00:51:51,318
Papa.

669
00:51:51,491 --> 00:51:52,515
[SIGHS]

670
00:51:52,692 --> 00:51:54,091
How's he doing?

671
00:51:54,261 --> 00:51:55,785
Hasn't quite gotten the hang of it yet.

672
00:51:55,962 --> 00:51:59,363
[PLAYERS YELLING]

673
00:52:01,301 --> 00:52:03,064
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

674
00:52:03,937 --> 00:52:05,029
COTTON:
Mike, son.

675
00:52:05,205 --> 00:52:07,298
Shuck the blocker, don't tote him!

676
00:52:07,474 --> 00:52:09,408
QB:
Set, go!

677
00:52:10,811 --> 00:52:14,440
No, no, no! No, no, no!

678
00:52:15,182 --> 00:52:16,740
QB:
Set, go!

679
00:52:25,458 --> 00:52:27,255
Balloons! They're balloons!

680
00:52:27,894 --> 00:52:30,829
Guys, quit looking at the balloons.
Everybody!

681
00:52:30,997 --> 00:52:33,864
COTTON: Most kids from bad situations
can't wait to be violent...

682
00:52:34,034 --> 00:52:35,661
...and that comes out on the field.

683
00:52:35,836 --> 00:52:38,999
But this kid, he acts like
he doesn't wanna hit anyone.

684
00:52:39,172 --> 00:52:41,072
He's Ferdinand the Bull.

685
00:52:41,241 --> 00:52:42,970
COTTON: What?
- Nothing.

686
00:52:44,477 --> 00:52:49,039
I thought he was gonna be a player. I can't
believe I used up all my chips to get him in.

687
00:52:49,216 --> 00:52:51,377
I thought you said
it was your Christian duty.

688
00:52:53,086 --> 00:52:55,782
Look, Bert, he's never even played before.

689
00:52:56,857 --> 00:53:00,156
Yeah, and he won't this fall if he
doesn't improve a lot before then.

690
00:53:00,493 --> 00:53:02,358
Who died and made him Bear Bryant?

691
00:53:02,529 --> 00:53:03,894
[LAUGHS]

692
00:53:04,064 --> 00:53:05,429
Unbelievable.

693
00:53:06,566 --> 00:53:08,693
Oh, God bless me.

694
00:53:08,869 --> 00:53:10,530
This is your summer workout sheet.

695
00:53:10,704 --> 00:53:12,934
Now, first it says to warm up
and get loose.

696
00:53:13,874 --> 00:53:15,637
Well, go ahead, get loose.

697
00:53:18,511 --> 00:53:20,069
Are you loose?

698
00:53:20,447 --> 00:53:24,213
Okay. Next, it's five 100-yard runs
to stretch out your legs.

699
00:53:24,384 --> 00:53:26,648
- Can we just go home and play video games?
- Look!

700
00:53:26,820 --> 00:53:29,983
Everybody at Wingate is expecting you
to be a star football player.

701
00:53:30,156 --> 00:53:31,783
Don't wanna let them down,
do you?

702
00:53:31,958 --> 00:53:33,892
- I don't know.
- What about Dad and Mom?

703
00:53:34,060 --> 00:53:36,722
Because, you see, in our family,
everyone's an athlete.

704
00:53:36,897 --> 00:53:40,958
Dad was a basketball star.
Collins plays volleyball and runs track.

705
00:53:41,134 --> 00:53:43,466
And me, well, as you know, I do it all.

706
00:53:43,637 --> 00:53:46,128
And Mom... Well, Mom was a cheerleader...

707
00:53:46,306 --> 00:53:50,037
...which doesn't exactly count,
but don't tell her I said that. Okay?

708
00:53:50,210 --> 00:53:52,371
- Okay.
- Okay.

709
00:53:52,545 --> 00:53:53,807
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

710
00:53:53,980 --> 00:53:57,040
- Yeah. Fifty.
MICHAEL: Uhn.

711
00:53:57,217 --> 00:53:59,151
SJ:
Fifty-one.

712
00:53:59,486 --> 00:54:02,819
Fifty-two. Fifty-three.

713
00:54:03,023 --> 00:54:06,186
Come on, you can get him.
Go, go, go! Come on!

714
00:54:06,359 --> 00:54:07,849
Five seconds left in the game!

715
00:54:09,729 --> 00:54:11,196
This way!

716
00:54:11,364 --> 00:54:12,524
This way!

717
00:54:12,699 --> 00:54:17,136
High knees, high knees, high knees!
