01:24:17,062 --> 01:24:20,498
All right, y'all keep practicing.
Remember, point your toes.

1191
01:24:20,665 --> 01:24:25,659
PLAYERS: One, two, three, one! One, two,
three, two! One, two, three, three!

1192
01:24:25,837 --> 01:24:27,998
You gonna buckle up today, son?

1193
01:24:30,308 --> 01:24:33,675
Shoot, man, Fulmer's here.
Might as well go home.

1194
01:24:33,845 --> 01:24:36,973
What do you say, fellas? Doing
all right? Good to see everybody.

1195
01:24:37,149 --> 01:24:39,413
Came all the way from Knoxville
to see for myself.

1196
01:24:39,584 --> 01:24:42,712
Heck, coach, we drove from Clemson,
nine hours.

1197
01:24:42,888 --> 01:24:44,480
Coach Fulmer. It's a real honor.

1198
01:24:44,656 --> 01:24:47,591
My pleasure. I've watched your program.
You've done really well.

1199
01:24:47,759 --> 01:24:50,887
I don't think there's any question
you'll be at the next level soon.

1200
01:24:51,062 --> 01:24:53,895
Oh, well, you know, we do
what we can with what we've got.

1201
01:24:54,766 --> 01:24:57,360
Is that...? Is that Michael? Is that O'Hare?

1202
01:24:57,536 --> 01:25:01,802
It's Oher. Like a paddle in a boat. Oher.

1203
01:25:05,443 --> 01:25:08,344
You think we might see some drills,
perhaps?

1204
01:25:08,513 --> 01:25:12,574
- I think all the coaches would appreciate it.
- Oh, yes, sir. You bet.

1205
01:25:13,618 --> 01:25:14,642
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

1206
01:25:14,820 --> 01:25:16,685
Listen up, fellas!
We're gonna do a board drill.

1207
01:25:16,855 --> 01:25:19,346
Big Mike,
Jay Collis, best on best right here.

1208
01:25:19,524 --> 01:25:21,219
Let's go, come on, come on!

1209
01:25:21,393 --> 01:25:23,384
[PLAYERS YELLING]

1210
01:25:29,367 --> 01:25:30,459
On the whistle, men.

1211
01:25:42,981 --> 01:25:44,471
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

1212
01:25:44,649 --> 01:25:45,911
[GRUNTING]

1213
01:25:46,084 --> 01:25:47,779
[CROWD YELLING]

1214
01:25:50,922 --> 01:25:51,946
Wow.

1215
01:25:53,225 --> 01:25:56,217
[PHONES BEEP]

1216
01:25:58,997 --> 01:26:00,021
Coach. Thank you.

1217
01:26:00,198 --> 01:26:03,099
- Where are you off to, coach?
- Back to South Carolina.

1218
01:26:03,268 --> 01:26:07,329
You tell Michael Oher, if he can qualify
with the grades, Clemson wants him.

1219
01:26:07,505 --> 01:26:09,735
Yeah, good luck with that, Brad.

1220
01:26:09,908 --> 01:26:11,967
You've done a great job
with this young man.

1221
01:26:12,143 --> 01:26:14,338
He was a little raw
when we first got him...

1222
01:26:14,512 --> 01:26:16,946
...but we've, you know,
coached him up a little bit.

1223
01:26:20,051 --> 01:26:22,110
Where is that?

1224
01:26:22,287 --> 01:26:25,654
Well, make me guess.

1225
01:26:27,559 --> 01:26:28,583
Hello, Mama.

1226
01:26:28,760 --> 01:26:31,558
Did you know to be eligible
for a Division I scholarship...

1227
01:26:31,730 --> 01:26:35,826
...Michael will need to make a 2.5 GPA?
- Really?

1228
01:26:36,001 --> 01:26:40,529
His ACT is low and I don't see it getting
any better if he retakes it. Right there.

1229
01:26:40,705 --> 01:26:41,967
Well, what's his GPA now?

1230
01:26:42,140 --> 01:26:44,665
1.76.

1231
01:26:44,843 --> 01:26:47,107
That's not bad when you
consider where he started.

1232
01:26:47,279 --> 01:26:49,645
Well, he's gonna have to
make all A's this year.

1233
01:26:50,148 --> 01:26:53,743
I'm serious.
And that might not even be enough.

1234
01:26:53,919 --> 01:26:55,511
So he goes to a junior college.

1235
01:26:56,221 --> 01:26:59,122
Unh-uhn. Most inner-city kids that
go to JC drop out in the first year.

1236
01:26:59,291 --> 01:27:01,555
And his shot at the pros
would go out the window.

1237
01:27:01,726 --> 01:27:04,786
Pros? Are we even sure
he's gonna get college offers?

1238
01:27:07,966 --> 01:27:10,457
NICK [OVER MACHINE]:
Michael, Nick Saban from LSU.

1239
01:27:10,635 --> 01:27:13,001
Looking forward to you
coming down and visiting.

1240
01:27:13,171 --> 01:27:16,140
LOU: Greetings, I'm Lou Holtz
from South Carolina. I'm call...

1241
01:27:16,308 --> 01:27:19,800
MAN: We are very interested in having
Michael over to Knoxville for a visit.

1242
01:27:21,046 --> 01:27:22,274
Phil Fulmer, Tennessee.

1243
01:27:22,447 --> 01:27:26,850
There's 20 more of them on there.
And these things right here, 50 of them.

1244
01:27:27,018 --> 01:27:28,485
- Any of those from Ole Miss?
- No.

1245
01:27:28,653 --> 01:27:31,588
They're not gonna start recruiting
till they hire another coach.

1246
01:27:31,756 --> 01:27:35,487
Doesn't make any difference
unless Michael makes his grades. Ahem.

1247
01:27:36,861 --> 01:27:37,885
What are we gonna do?

1248
01:27:40,011 --> 01:27:43,105
I understand you applied
for a teaching position at Wingate.

1249
01:27:44,348 --> 01:27:46,145
I wasn't religious enough for them.

1250
01:27:46,784 --> 01:27:52,347
I'm a spiritual person, Mrs. Tuohy,
but I have certain, shall we say, doubts.

1251
01:27:53,424 --> 01:27:55,449
Well, I appreciate your honesty,
Miss Sue.

1252
01:27:55,826 --> 01:27:57,418
What's the situation with Michael?

1253
01:27:57,595 --> 01:28:00,063
- He needs to do better in school.
- Obviously.

1254
01:28:00,231 --> 01:28:01,493
But why the big push?

1255
01:28:01,665 --> 01:28:05,726
Well, he's in line for a football
scholarship if he gets his grades up.

1256
01:28:05,903 --> 01:28:09,066
- Is he considering Ole Miss?
- Better be.

1257
01:28:10,474 --> 01:28:12,032
I'd love to work with him.

1258
01:28:12,209 --> 01:28:14,609
Well, when would you like to start?

1259
01:28:15,479 --> 01:28:19,347
Mrs. Tuohy, um, there's something
you should know about me.

1260
01:28:19,517 --> 01:28:21,212
I don't usually tell many people...

1261
01:28:21,385 --> 01:28:25,048
...but it's something I feel you should
be aware of before you hire me.

1262
01:28:25,723 --> 01:28:27,782
Uh... What is it?

1263
01:28:28,692 --> 01:28:30,216
I'm a Democrat.

1264
01:28:32,363 --> 01:28:34,126
Okay.

1265
01:28:39,403 --> 01:28:41,928
- I don't understand it.
- Yet.

1266
01:28:42,106 --> 01:28:44,370
You don't understand it yet.

1267
01:28:46,177 --> 01:28:47,667
How big is your head, Michael?

1268
01:28:47,912 --> 01:28:49,243
Big.

1269
01:28:49,413 --> 01:28:50,846
And what's in there?

1270
01:28:51,015 --> 01:28:52,312
- A brain.
- A brain.

1271
01:28:52,483 --> 01:28:54,178
It's full of knowledge.

1272
01:28:54,351 --> 01:28:58,981
Like a file cabinet with maps,
and shortcuts for figuring things out.

1273
01:28:59,657 --> 01:29:03,491
You'll get there, Michael Oher, because
I'm here to help you use those maps...

1274
01:29:03,661 --> 01:29:07,688
...and reach your destination,
like Sacagawea led Lewis and Clark.

1275
01:29:07,865 --> 01:29:09,093
Sacagawea?

1276
01:29:09,266 --> 01:29:12,633
We'll get to that.
And the history books have it wrong.

1277
01:29:12,803 --> 01:29:16,000
All you need to know
is I'll get you there.

1278
01:29:16,807 --> 01:29:18,798
Do you believe me?

1279
01:29:21,579 --> 01:29:23,206
You trust me, Michael?

1280
01:29:25,449 --> 01:29:26,473
Yes, Miss Sue.

1281
01:29:29,320 --> 01:29:30,514
Try it again.

1282
01:29:32,056 --> 01:29:34,889
What's the next one? Read that
to me. Okay, what does it say?

1283
01:29:35,059 --> 01:29:39,496
First we have to find the constant.
Now, where is the constant?

1284
01:29:40,097 --> 01:29:42,258
Good. See?

1285
01:29:42,433 --> 01:29:45,630
Who'd have thought we'd have
a black son before we knew a Democrat?

1286
01:29:45,803 --> 01:29:47,361
[DOORBELL RINGS]

1287
01:29:47,805 --> 01:29:51,002
LEIGH ANNE: Doorbell!
SEAN: I got it, guys.

1288
01:29:53,611 --> 01:29:55,670
Coach, how are you? Come in.
Sean Tuohy.

1289
01:29:55,846 --> 01:29:58,644
- Nick Saban, nice to meet you.
- Nice to see you. My pleasure.

1290
01:29:58,816 --> 01:30:01,080
I appreciate the opportunity
to come in your home.

1291
01:30:01,252 --> 01:30:03,686
- This is my daughter, Collins.
- Pleasure to meet you.

1292
01:30:03,854 --> 01:30:06,721
- And you must be Leigh Anne.
- That would be me, Coach Saban.

1293
01:30:06,891 --> 01:30:08,324
- Nice to meet you.
- You too.

1294
01:30:08,492 --> 01:30:10,983
Just call me Nick.
This is an incredible home.

1295
01:30:11,162 --> 01:30:13,392
The Windsor valances are a nice touch.

1296
01:30:13,564 --> 01:30:17,557
Well, thank you.
You obviously have excellent taste.

1297
01:30:17,735 --> 01:30:19,669
NICK:
Well, we appreciate quality...

1298
01:30:19,837 --> 01:30:21,702
...and recognize it when we see it.

1299
01:30:23,274 --> 01:30:25,674
Michael, why don't you come in
and say hello?

1300
01:30:25,843 --> 01:30:28,175
- Nick Saban. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

1301
01:30:28,345 --> 01:30:30,438
NICK: And you must be SJ.
- That's me.

1302
01:30:30,614 --> 01:30:34,015
Michael, why don't you and Nick
go into the living room and talk?

1303
01:30:34,351 --> 01:30:35,477
Can SJ come?

1304
01:30:35,653 --> 01:30:38,679
- Absolutely. We'll recruit the both of you.
- All right.

1305
01:30:41,692 --> 01:30:43,853
I find him extremely handsome.

1306
01:30:44,028 --> 01:30:45,928
Yeah, I'm right here, Leigh Anne.

1307
01:30:46,096 --> 01:30:47,620
Yeah, I know.

1308
01:30:47,798 --> 01:30:50,790
NICK: So, Michael, we would love
to get you down to LSU for a visit.

1309
01:30:50,968 --> 01:30:52,936
We've got a great thing going
right now.

1310
01:30:53,103 --> 01:30:56,561
You have an opportunity to be
successful as a person, as a student...

1311
01:30:56,740 --> 01:31:00,972
...and an opportunity to be a part of the
next national championship team at LSU.

1312
01:31:01,145 --> 01:31:04,171
So, what do you say?
Would you like to commit to a visit?

1313
01:31:04,348 --> 01:31:05,781
SJ: Can I ask a question?
NICK: Sure.

1314
01:31:06,116 --> 01:31:09,643
My brother and I are very close,
and so...

1315
01:31:09,820 --> 01:31:14,655
...I'm very afraid that if he goes off
to school, I might not get to see him.

1316
01:31:14,825 --> 01:31:16,486
- So...
- Go on.

1317
01:31:16,660 --> 01:31:20,460
I guess I was just wondering
how much access I'd have to him.

1318
01:31:20,631 --> 01:31:23,065
NICK: Well, SJ, you would have
total access to Michael.

1319
01:31:23,234 --> 01:31:26,328
But better than that, in his first game
in Tiger Stadium...

1320
01:31:26,503 --> 01:31:29,267
...we would like for you to lead
the team out of the tunnel.

1321
01:31:29,440 --> 01:31:31,840
- What do you think about that?
- Sounds good.

1322
01:31:34,445 --> 01:31:36,436
[CROWD CHEERING]

1323
01:31:39,416 --> 01:31:41,407
[GRUNTING]

1324
01:31:43,420 --> 01:31:45,354
[DOORBELL RINGS]

1325
01:31:46,323 --> 01:31:47,517
Come on in.

1326
01:31:47,691 --> 01:31:50,888
Greetings. I'm Lou Holtz from
the University of South Carolina.

1327
01:31:51,061 --> 01:31:54,030
Leigh Anne Tuohy. Nice to meet you.
Come on in. Michael?

1328
01:31:54,198 --> 01:31:56,325
Hello. I'm Tommy Tuberville,
Auburn University.

1329
01:31:56,500 --> 01:31:58,695
Leigh Anne Tuohy. Nice to meet you.
Michael?

1330
01:31:58,869 --> 01:32:02,327
- Houston Nutt, University of Arkansas.
- Leigh Anne Tuohy. Nice to meet you.

1331
01:32:02,506 --> 01:32:05,031
- Ole Miss cup, huh?
- Michael?

1332
01:32:06,010 --> 01:32:07,034
[SIGHS]

1333
01:32:07,211 --> 01:32:09,475
Oh, come on. You know this.

1334
01:32:09,647 --> 01:32:11,376
It's logical.

1335
01:32:22,626 --> 01:32:25,186
I guarantee, you come to
University of South Carolina...

1336
01:32:25,362 --> 01:32:27,853
...it'll be the smartest decision
you've ever made.

1337
01:32:28,032 --> 01:32:31,661
We want you, we need you,
but the other thing is, Mike, you need us.

1338
01:32:35,406 --> 01:32:36,430
Ow!

1339
01:32:36,607 --> 01:32:39,542
Knoxville is a tremendous place
to live and...

1340
01:32:39,710 --> 01:32:42,702
HOUSTON: I know there's Lions,
there's Tigers, there's Bears.

1341
01:32:42,880 --> 01:32:45,007
Hey, there's only one Razorback
in the world.

1342
01:32:45,182 --> 01:32:48,913
And not only that, you will look great
in Gamecock red.

1343
01:32:49,086 --> 01:32:50,110
What's in it for me?

1344
01:32:50,287 --> 01:32:53,984
SJ, I'm gonna get you a hog hat
and the whole family a hog hat.

1345
01:32:54,158 --> 01:32:56,285
Are you telling me that's
the best you can do?

1346
01:32:56,460 --> 01:32:58,758
SJ, you remind me of me as a boy.

1347
01:32:58,929 --> 01:33:01,295
Coach, help me help you.

1348
01:33:01,465 --> 01:33:04,992
I can give you a Gamecock headdress,
and with real feathers.

1349
01:33:13,777 --> 01:33:17,178
- What do you got for me, Phil?
- I've been thinking a lot about that...

1350
01:33:17,348 --> 01:33:19,942
...and one of the things
I think would be special...

1351
01:33:20,117 --> 01:33:24,110
...is we'll walk arm-in-arm to the center
of Neyland Stadium in the first ball game...

1352
01:33:24,288 --> 01:33:26,620
...and do the coin toss together.
How's that sound?

1353
01:33:26,790 --> 01:33:29,258
Coach Fulmer, it's a pleasure
doing business with you.

1354
01:33:29,426 --> 01:33:32,224
My pleasure, CJ. You bet you, buddy.

1355
01:33:32,396 --> 01:33:34,364
[CROWD CHEERING]

1356
01:33:40,771 --> 01:33:41,795
[DOORBELL RINGS]

1357
01:33:42,539 --> 01:33:44,063
Congratulations on getting hired.

1358
01:33:44,241 --> 01:33:47,005
Thank you, ma'am.
Ole Miss is my dream job.

1359
01:33:47,177 --> 01:33:50,305
You're coming a little late to the party
and we're diehard Rebels...

1360
01:33:50,481 --> 01:33:52,915
...so I'm gonna pretty much
give you a road map.

1361
01:33:53,083 --> 01:33:54,710
- Got it.
- LSU is out.

1362
01:33:54,885 --> 01:33:56,876
Everybody knows Saban's
going to the NFL.

1363
01:33:57,054 --> 01:33:59,852
Don't wanna name names,
but on Michael's first two trips...

1364
01:34:00,023 --> 01:34:02,287
...somebody took him to a titty bar.
- Terrible.

1365
01:34:02,459 --> 01:34:04,654
Tell me about it.
He had nightmares for weeks.

1366
01:34:04,828 --> 01:34:07,126
So when he visits,
I want you to feed him Italian.

1367
01:34:07,297 --> 01:34:09,891
He likes fettuccine Alfredo.
And take him to a movie.

1368
01:34:10,067 --> 01:34:13,298
Not Chainsaw Massacre
because he'll just cover his eyes.

1369
01:34:13,470 --> 01:34:15,870
Then get him in bed by 10. Got it?

1370
01:34:16,039 --> 01:34:17,233
- Yes, ma'am.
- All right.

1371
01:34:17,408 --> 01:34:19,239
- What about Tennessee?
- Mm.

1372
01:34:19,576 --> 01:34:21,407
Breaks my heart,
but they're still in the hunt.

1373
01:34:21,578 --> 01:34:23,944
Ahem. Fulmer made SJ a sweet deal.

1374
01:34:24,114 --> 01:34:26,674
- I hear that kid can really pepper the gumbo.
- Hmm.

1375
01:34:26,850 --> 01:34:29,580
He's his daddy's boy. You ready?

1376
01:34:29,753 --> 01:34:31,653
- Let's do it.
- All right.

1377
01:34:31,822 --> 01:34:34,256
ED: Mike, do you love barbecue?
I tell you what, Mike.

1378
01:34:34,425 --> 01:34:37,883
You can go to a gas station and
get the best barbecue you ever got.

1379
01:34:38,061 --> 01:34:39,528
It's a wonderful place to live.

1380
01:34:39,696 --> 01:34:43,860
Fried catfish, all the good food that
we love to eat and that's not good for us...

1381
01:34:44,034 --> 01:34:46,298
...you can have it there, Mike,
I promise you.

1382
01:34:46,470 --> 01:34:48,768
And for you, SJ, this is what I can do.

1383
01:34:48,939 --> 01:34:51,032
At Ole Miss, we have
The Grove by the stadium.

1384
01:34:51,208 --> 01:34:54,609
We walk it before every game
in front of thousands of people.

1385
01:34:54,778 --> 01:34:56,678
It's a sacred ritual. And I'm in front.

1386
01:34:57,214 --> 01:34:59,114
Seen it a thousand times.

1387
01:34:59,283 --> 01:35:03,049
Ever seen it from the front of the line?
Next year, you and me, leading the team.

1388
01:35:03,220 --> 01:35:07,156
Tennessee offered to let me
run on the field and flip the coin.

1389
01:35:10,093 --> 01:35:12,152
I'll throw in a sideline pass.

1390
01:35:22,439 --> 01:35:23,872
Have you decided yet, Michael?

1391
01:35:24,641 --> 01:35:26,541
No, Miss Sue.

1392
01:35:27,311 --> 01:35:29,677
But you like Tennessee?

1393
01:35:30,647 --> 01:35:31,978
Yeah. That's a good school.

1394
01:35:33,083 --> 01:35:35,074
Not at the academic level of Ole Miss...

1395
01:35:35,252 --> 01:35:38,244
...but they have a outstanding
Science Department.

1396
01:35:39,122 --> 01:35:41,352
You know what they're famous for?

1397
01:35:41,792 --> 01:35:44,056
They work with the FBI...

1398
01:35:44,228 --> 01:35:48,187
...to study the effects of soil
on decomposing body parts.

1399
01:35:48,365 --> 01:35:50,060
What's that mean?

1400
01:35:50,234 --> 01:35:53,692
Well, when they find a body, the police
wanna know how long it's been dead.

1401
01:35:53,871 --> 01:35:56,806
So the fine folks at Tennessee
help them out.

1402
01:35:57,608 --> 01:36:00,304
Oh, they have lots of body parts.

1403
01:36:00,511 --> 01:36:04,572
Arms and legs and hands...

1404
01:36:04,748 --> 01:36:07,273
...from hospitals and medical schools.

1405
01:36:07,851 --> 01:36:09,148
[CHUCKLES]

1406
01:36:10,053 --> 01:36:11,918
And do you know where they store them?

1407
01:36:15,859 --> 01:36:18,020
Right underneath the football field.

1408
01:36:20,197 --> 01:36:24,725
So while it's fine and dandy
to have 100,000 fans cheering for you...

1409
01:36:24,902 --> 01:36:29,532
...the bodies you should be worried about
are the ones right under the turf.

1410
01:36:29,706 --> 01:36:32,800
Set to poke up through the ground
and grab you.

1411
01:36:37,614 --> 01:36:40,583
Well, it's your decision
where you wanna play ball.

1412
01:36:40,751 --> 01:36:42,946
Don't let me influence you.

1413
01:36:52,729 --> 01:36:54,162
[APPLAUSE]

1414
01:37:11,615 --> 01:37:14,880
All the other teachers are on board.
I don't know what your problem is.

1415
01:37:15,052 --> 01:37:18,988
I'm sorry. I will not give a student
a grade he or she doesn't deserve.

